text.text:
We're finally in sight of fixing the hellish developer experience and research-to-production path in ML. It starts with software engineering fundamentals: Decoupling systems to be able to iterate, debug, and version them independently.

This was the original hypothesis that led me to leave Meta to work on Runhouse full time. Please share with your ML Engineer and Data Scientist friends who will pearl-clutch and share their strongly-worded opinions üëäüëäüëä

https://lnkd.in/eJUTratG
